memory :- i.  process isolation
          ii. automatic allocation and mangement.
          iii. Support of modular programming.
          iv. protection and access control.
          v. Long term storage.

virtual Memory:- 
        i.  Implements long term storage.
        ii. Information stored in named objects called files.
        iii.Allows programmers to address memory from a logical point of view.

Paging :- 
      i.  Allow processes to be compromised of a number of fixed size block called pages.
      ii. address of page is the page number and the offset within the page.
      iii.each page may be located anywhere in the main memory.
      iv. Real address and physical address is the main memory address.
      
